episodes.title: Finn the Human
episodes.plot: Finn's wish to stop the evil Lich has massive cosmic consequences.

episodes.title: Jake the Dog
episodes.plot: Following the unexpected consequences of Finn's cosmic wish it's up to the Jake -- and his short attention span -- to set things right.

episodes.title: Five More Short Graybles
episodes.plot: Five more short stories with one connecting theme.

episodes.title: Up a Tree
episodes.plot: Having been magical shrunk to the size of a forest animal, Finn takes up a quest to climb a tree and retrieve his lost flying disc.

episodes.title: All the Little People
episodes.plot: Finn receives a mysterious bag that contains what appears to be living toys of everyone he knows, which playing with has unexpected results.

episodes.title: Jake the Dad
episodes.plot: Lady gives birth to a litter of puppies and Jake becomes an eager but frantic father.

episodes.title: Davey
episodes.plot: Finn becomes Davey, an alter-ego, everyman in order to escape the attention of fame and becomes consumed by his new identity.

episodes.title: Mystery Dungeon
episodes.plot: Ice King, Neptr, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab wake up in a dungeon and must work together to escape.

episodes.title: All Your Fault
episodes.plot: Lemongrab sends a distress message to the Candy Kingdom which Finn and Jake respond to.

episodes.title: Little Dude
episodes.plot: Finn's hat comes to life.

episodes.title: Bad Little Boy
episodes.plot: A return to the gender-swapped world with Fionna and Cake and Marshall Lee the Vampire King.

episodes.title: Vault of Bones
episodes.plot: Finn and Flame Princess explore a dungeon together.

episodes.title: The Great Bird Man
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake get lost in the badlands and are saved by Xergiok, ex-Goblin King who now lives in a cave. A look at what Ice King and Marceline were like 996 years ago.

episodes.title: Simon & Marcy
episodes.plot: Marceline tells Finn and Jake about her and Ice King's past, 996 years ago.

episodes.title: A Glitch Is a Glitch
episodes.plot: Ice King creates a computer virus to delete everybody except him and Princess Bubblegum. Stuck inside the treehouse during a sword storm, Jake builds a pillow fort while Finn goes to a different world.

episodes.title: Puhoy
episodes.plot: Depressed by his feelings with Flame Princess, Finn enters a pillow fort where he enters a new world and makes a new life for himself.

episodes.title: BMO Lost
episodes.plot: BMO gets snatched away by a giant eagle and must find his way home.

episodes.title: Princess Potluck
episodes.plot: Ice King does everything possible to ruin a princess potluck he believes he didn't get invited to.

episodes.title: James Baxter the Horse
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake meet a horse with the power to make sad people happy.

episodes.title: Shh!
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake hold a contest to see who can last longer without talking.

episodes.title: The Suitor
episodes.plot: Peppermint Butler thinks Princess Bubblegum is spending too much time in her lab and decides she needs a suitor.

episodes.title: The Party's Over, Isla de Señorita
episodes.plot: After becoming tired of always losing to Finn and Jake and failing to win Princess Bubblegum's love, Ice King decides to throw in the towel.

episodes.title: One Last Job
episodes.plot: Jake Jr. gets mixed up with some bad eggs, and Jake reunites with his old gang to save her.

episodes.title: Another Five More Short Graybles
episodes.plot: Five short stories, some involving Finn and Jake building a time machine.

episodes.title: Candy Streets
episodes.plot: Lumpy Space Princess is robbed and faints before she can tell Finn and Jake who robbed her.

episodes.title: Wizards Only, Fools
episodes.plot: Princess Bubblegum believes magic is nothing but a bunch of hooey until Starchy gets sick.

episodes.title: Jakesuit
episodes.plot: Jake is sick and tired of Finn using his body as a suit of armor.

episodes.title: Be More
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake disguise themselves as MOs in order to infiltrate the MO factory.

episodes.title: Sky Witch
episodes.plot: Princess Bubblegum and Marceline team up to reclaim lost property.

episodes.title: Frost & Fire
episodes.plot: After Flame Princess battles Ice King, Finn has an exciting dream.

episodes.title: Too Old
episodes.plot: Finn and Princess Bubblegum discover a talented lemon citizen named Lemonhope while on a diplomatic trip to Castle Lemongrab; also, something strange is happening to the Earls of Lemongrab, leading to their society crumbling.

episodes.title: Earth & Water
episodes.plot: Princess Bubblegum subjects Flame Princess to a series of tests to gauge Fire Princess' fiery tendencies.

episodes.title: Time Sandwich
episodes.plot: Jake crafts the most delicious sandwich ever.

episodes.title: The Vault
episodes.plot: Jake and BMO help Finn tap into his repressed memories to uncover a secret past.

episodes.title: Love Games
episodes.plot: Slime Princess needs a husband or else she'll lose the Slime Kingdom to her obnoxious sister.

episodes.title: Dungeon Train
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake discover a train where every car is a dungeon filled with a new foe for Finn to fight.

episodes.title: Box Prince
episodes.plot: Finn meets the Box Prince (a cat with a box on its back) and discovers the Box Kingdom has been taken over by an impostor.

episodes.title: Red Starved
episodes.plot: Finn, Jake and Marceline become trapped underground. Starving for anything red Marceline begins to loose control and turns her eyes to Finn and Jake's blood.

episodes.title: We Fixed a Truck
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake find a broken down pickup truck and enlist the help of BMO and Banana Man to fix it.

episodes.title: Play Date
episodes.plot: Sick and tired of babysitting Ice King while the Ice Kingdom is being rebuilt, Finn and Jake call up an old friend to hang out with their annoying houseguest: Abracadaniel. But when Ice King and his new BFF accidentally unleash the demon Kee-Oth, Finn and Jake have to clean up their mess.

episodes.title: The Pit
episodes.plot: Kee-Oth the Blood Demon has kidnapped Jake, taken him back to his dimension and thrown him in a pit. If Finn wants to rescue his friend, he's going to need Lady Rainicorn's help... and a videotape that will reveal how to open the portal to Kee-Oth's messed-up dimension.

episodes.title: James
episodes.plot: Finn and Jake accompany Princess Bubblegum on her study of the Desert of Wonders. However, they are soon attacked by goo monsters, and Finn and Jake think that Bubblegum's robot helper James is to blame.

episodes.title: Root Beer Guy
episodes.plot: Root beer guy must put aside his common everyday life to search for the truth behind the murders, lies, and deceit in the Candy Kingdom.

episodes.title: Apple Wedding
episodes.plot: Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig are getting married.

episodes.title: Blade of Grass
episodes.plot: Finn gets a new sword.

episodes.title: Rattleballs
episodes.plot: Finn meets an old robot in the junkyard who promises to make Finn into a master swordsman.

episodes.title: The Red Throne
episodes.plot: The Fire King and Don John the Flame Lord take over the Fire Kingdom. Now Flame Princess must use Finn's and Cinnamon Bun's help to get it back.

episodes.title: Betty
episodes.plot: The Ice King loses his powers, reverts to his old human-self, and begins to wither away due to being over a thousand years old.

episodes.title: Bad Timing
episodes.plot: Bubblegum Princess invents a time travel sphere that Lumpy Space Princess wants for solving her relationship problems.

episodes.title: Lemonhope Part One
episodes.plot: Young Lemonhope leaves the candy kingdom after a deep desire to be free of all responsibilities grips him. So he ventures out on his own with nothing more than a lute and hope to find freedom.

episodes.title: Lemonhope Part Two
episodes.plot: Lemonhope meets an adventurer who teaches him true freedom. But even with his new life of freedom he is plagued with dreams of his lemon kingdom and his family being imprisoned.

episodes.title: Billy's Bucket List
episodes.plot: Finn meets Billy's ex-girlfriend, Canyon, who finds Billy's bucket list. Finn vows to complete it for his late hero.
